<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870603-0041 </DOCNO><HL> Unit of Aegon Says MoreOf Its Shares Purchased</HL><DD> 06/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LINV AEGNYBUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK) </IN><DATELINE> CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Life Investors Inc. said it and another unit of a Dutch insurance company purchased 451,000 Life Investors common shares for $51.61 each, or $23.3 million.    The insurance concern said the shares were purchased under a joint tender offer for any and all of its shares outstanding. As reported, Life Investors and Aegon N.V. have made a series of tender offers since 1981 under a plan to take the company private by 1988. Currently, Aegon owns 95% of Life Investors' 8.6 million common shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>